title: Grateful Dead Live at Kansas City Municipal Auditorium Arena on 1980-08-17
description: Jack Straw-> Sugaree, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Peggy-O, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Far From Me, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance Don't Ease Me In, Samson & Delilah, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Alright i'm not a deadhead at all so when the dead came to the archive i didn't really care. This is the first one i've listened to, since I know my taping history and I wanted to hear what the hub-bub was about .. Overall, not too impressed. 

Show Quality: 3 of 5 stars. Alight, but i don't hear anything legendary. the jams are fun, but nothing amazing.

Sound Quality: 3 of 5 stars. There are stage technical difficulties, and the audience source is not too amazing. The guitar is very strong but the drums and the rest of the instruments are barely hearable, including the vocals, and it does have it's share of light crowd noise.. 

I'll give GD another shot with another streaming show, but i wasn't too stoked on this show. thanks archive.org for the streaming option to hear a show without downloading it first!

not the best show I would have to agree with the comments of the other reviewer_ but because I drove 200 miles to see this show plus I taped it with a "toy" recorder from the 17th row it was nice to hear anything that was better than the cassettes I had which replaced my master years ago so for me I would have to give it 5 stars just for the memories
